I"è<h1 id="setting-up-the-environment-and-making-a-hello-world-program">Setting up the environment and making a ‚ÄúHello World‚Äù program</h1>

<p>Android Studio is the official IDE for Android, so I obediently decided to use it!</p>

<ol>
  <li><a href="https://developer.android.com/studio/index.html">Install Android Studio</a> (Java is already installed, of course!).</li>
  <li>Create a new project with an ‚ÄúEmpty Activity‚Äù. By default, this should give a screen with ‚ÄúHello World‚Äù.</li>
  <li>Build the project.</li>
  <li>Install anything additional if prompted.</li>
  <li>Run the project and select an AVD (Android Virtual Device). I selected the default AVD and got an error. It stated that Vtx needed to be enabled in the BIOS. Vtx is to permit hardware acceleration for virtualization to run AVDs. I enabled this in the BIOS and rebooted.</li>
  <li>The AVD loaded this time but it didn‚Äôt display the program properly.</li>
  <li>I created a new AVD with a smaller screen size and it worked, but it gave a warning that there can be stability issues with my graphics device driver.</li>
</ol>

