<h1 id="how-to-run-the-app-on-my-phone">How to run the app on my phone</h1>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>You need to enable the Settings&gt;Developer Options&gt;USB Debugging option on your phone. I have Android 5.1.1 on my phone and I couldn‚Äôt find the Developer Options in Settings. After a bit of <a href="https://www.androidcentral.com/android-50-lollipop-basics-how-turn-developer-settings">research</a>, I discovered that you must go to Settings&gt;About phone and hit the build number 7 times to unlock Developer Options. Like a cheat code on a computer game! üòÄ</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Run the app as usual, just choose your phone from the list of AVDs and Android Studio will  install the app on your device and launch it! The app is installed on your phone, so when you disconnect, it is still there!</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h1 id="to-directly-install-the-app-on-your-phone">To directly install the app on your phone</h1>

<ul>
  <li>The apk is the packaged app and should be in ‚Äúproject folder\app\build\outputs\apk\debug‚Äù.</li>
  <li>Transfer this file onto your phone and open it, the installer will do the rest. üòÄ</li>
</ul>
